This paper involves the development of a flight control strategy for a hummingbird robot, which requires expertise in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of model-based nonlinear control and model-free reinforcement learning also suggests that this paper could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of visual stimuli, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
